Bootstrap usually refers to Bootstrap, a popular open-source framework used to build responsive and mobile-first websites quickly.
1. Key Features
Responsive Design → Websites adjust automatically to mobile, tablet, and desktop screens
Grid System → Easy layout creation using rows and columns
Pre-built Components → Buttons, forms, navbars, cards, modals, etc.
CSS Utilities → Quick styling (spacing, colors, alignment)
JavaScript Plugins → Interactive features like dropdowns, sliders, popups
2. Why Use Bootstrap?
Saves time in development
Ensures consistency in design
Works well across browsers
Beginner-friendly
3. Example Use

You can quickly create a webpage with a navbar, buttons, and layout using Bootstrap classes instead of writing full CSS.
